extends base.pug

append vars
	- title = "PiKVM / Download - Open and cheap DIY IP-KVM on Raspberry Pi"

block body
	div(class="content")
		div(class="block text-left")
			h3 Here you can find ready-made PiKVM images for Raspberry Pi
			hr
			| Download the appropriate memory card image for the #[a(target="_blank" href="https://github.com/pikvm/pikvm") PiKVM].
			| Select the image by the #[a(target="_blank" href=`${github_link}#required-hardware`) board, platform],
			| and the video capture device you are using.
			| #[br]#[br]
			| Minimum 16 Gb memory card class 10 is strongly recommended.
			hr
			h3 #[b Raspberry Pi 4], #[b v2] platform:
			ul
				li
					| For HDMI-to-CSI bridge: #[a(href="https://files.pikvm.org/images/v2-hdmi-rpi4-latest.img.bz2") #[b v2-hdmi-rpi4-latest.img.bz2]]
					| [#[a(href="https://files.pikvm.org/images/v2-hdmi-rpi4-latest.img.bz2.sha1") SHA-1]]
				li
					| For HDMI-to-USB dongle: #[a(href="https://files.pikvm.org/images/v2-hdmiusb-rpi4-latest.img.bz2") #[b v2-hdmiusb-rpi4-latest.img.bz2]]
					| [#[a(href="https://files.pikvm.org/images/v2-hdmiusb-rpi4-latest.img.bz2.sha1") SHA-1]]
			h3 #[b Raspberry Pi Zero W], #[b v2] platform:
			ul
				li
					| For HDMI-to-CSI bridge: #[a(href="https://files.pikvm.org/images/v2-hdmi-zerow-latest.img.bz2") #[b v2-hdmi-zerow-latest.img.bz2]]
					| [#[a(href="https://files.pikvm.org/images/v2-hdmi-zerow-latest.img.bz2.sha1") SHA-1]]
			hr
			h3 #[b Raspberry Pi 4], #[b v3 HAT] platform:
			ul
				li
					| For v3 HAT Platform only: #[a(href="https://files.pikvm.org/images/v3-hdmi-rpi4-latest.img.bz2") #[b v3-hdmi-rpi4-latest.img.bz2]]
					| [#[a(href="https://files.pikvm.org/images/v3-hdmi-rpi4-latest.img.bz2.sha1") SHA-1]]
			| To flash the image #[a(target="_blank" href="https://docs.pikvm.org/flashing_os") follow the instructions].
			hr
			| Right now, pre-compiled images are only available for the Raspberry Pi 4 and ZeroW.
			| In all other cases, you will need to build the operating system yourself. But don't worry,
			| it's #[a(target="_blank" href="https://docs.pikvm.org/building_os") very simple].
			hr
			| #[a(target="_blank" href="https://files.pikvm.org/images") Images archive].
